#### Moderators

In this pre-registration, we will only report the moderator effects of gender and age to provide examples.

##### Gender

@fig-gender-secondary-outcomes and @tbl-gender-secondary-outcomes show the moderator effect of gender on the secondary outcomes.


::: {.cell}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![Predicted treatment effects on secondary outcomes by gender. Dots represent predicted effects within each gender category, whiskers depict 95% CIs without correction for multiple comparisons. Significance stars indicate whether the treatment effect in a given category differs significantly from zero, based on BH-adjusted p-values across 60 comparisons (20 interventions × 3 gender categories) within each outcome. Data are simulated at random, thus we should not expect to see any significant effects.](preregistration_files/figure-html/fig-gender-secondary-outcomes-1.png){#fig-gender-secondary-outcomes width=100%}
